        <p>
            This example is about the evolution of a specific indicator over time. 
            In order to keep it simple we will observe only 3 countries and compare them with the average over the European Union 27 countries.
        </p><p>
            Creation of the chart output with DAS:<br>
            <ol style="margin-left:3em">
                <li>First start the DAS Web Application: <a href="http://scoreboard.lod2.eu/index.php?scenario=2">Open DAS - Scenario 2</a></li>
                <li>Select the indicator <em>Households with access to the Internet at home</em> of indicatorgroup <em>Internet usage</em> in the respective selection box.
                <li>Select the countries <em>Belgium</em>, <em>European Union - 27 countries</em>, <em>France</em> and <em>Germany</em> in the country selector 
                (by default the <em>European Union - 27 countries</em> should still be selected).
            </ol>
            If you do not want to follow these steps you can click 
            <a href="http://scoreboard.lod2.eu/index.php?scenario=2&indicators%5B%5D=h_iacc+HH_TOTAL+%25_hh&countries%5B%5D=BE&countries%5B%5D=EU27&countries%5B%5D=FR&countries%5B%5D=DE#chart">here</a> 
            to jump directly to the output. 
            The result of this selection leads to a line-chart containing 4 lines representing the countries. 
            The temporal dimension is represented on the X-Axis, and the percentage values are put on the Y-Axis (compare with Figure 4). 
        </p><p>
            A similar output can be created with CubeViz:
            <ol style="margin-left:3em">
                <li>Start CubeViz as part of the Data Portal for the European Commission with the DAS DataCube: <a href="<?php echo $_REQUEST ['urlBase']; ?>?m=http://data.lod2.eu/scoreboard/">Start CubeViz with DAS DataCube</a></li>                
                <li>Select on the left side the Data Structure <em>per Indicator</em></li>
                <li>Select the Dataset <em>% of Housholds with Access to the Internet at home</em></li>
                <li>Select the elements <em>Belgium</em>, <em>European Union - 27 countries</em>, <em>France</em> and <em>Germany</em> of the dimension <em>Country</em> (click the Icon behind the dimension)</li>
                <li>Select all elements of the dimension <em>Year</em>. (click on the icon behind the dimension)</li>
                <li>Click on <em>Update Visualization</em></li>
                <li>The first rendered Chart is a bar-chart. To get a similar chart click on the top-right corner on the icon for the line-chart.</li>
                <li>Click again on the line-chart icon to open the <em>options dialogue</em> and configure there the type <em>spline</em> (and a <em>switch of the axes</em> if necessary)</li>
            </ol>
        </p><p>
            The result with CubeViz is quite similar to the output of DAS (compare Figure 3 and 4).
            In DAS the years are limited from 2004 until 2012, which can not be configured. 
            For France, data is missing for the Year 2005, which can be seen in both tools, but with different visualized elements. 
            Try out the Column and Polar charts with the same selection.
        </p>
